

class LFUCache {
    class Node{
    int key;
    int value;
    int freq;
    Node prev;
    Node next;

    public Node(int key , int value)
    {
        this.key = key;
        this.value = value;
        this.freq = 1;
    }

    }

    class DoublyLinkedList
    {
        Node head;
        Node tail;
        int size;

        public DoublyLinkedList()
        {
            head = new Node(0,0);
            tail = new Node(0,0);
            head.next = tail;
            tail.prev = head;
            size = 0;
        }

        public void addToHead(Node node)
        {
            node.next = head.next;
            node.prev = head;
            head.next.prev= node;
            head.next = node;
            size++;
        }

        public void remove(Node node)
        {
            node.prev.next = node.next;
            node.next.prev = node.prev;
            size--;
        }

        public Node removeTail()
        {
            if(size == 0) return null;

            Node node = tail.prev;
            remove(node);
            return node;
        }
    }

    int capacity;
    int minFreq;
    Map<Integer, Node> nodeMap;
    Map<Integer, DoublyLinkedList> freqMap;


    public LFUCache(int capacity) {

        this.capacity = capacity;
        this.minFreq = 0;
        this.nodeMap = new HashMap<>();
        this.freqMap = new HashMap<>();
        
    }
    
    public int get(int key) {

        if(!nodeMap.containsKey(key)) return -1;

        Node node= nodeMap.get(key);
        updateFrequency(node);
        return node.value;
        
    }
    
    public void put(int key, int value) {

        if(capacity == 0) return;

        if(nodeMap.containsKey(key))
        {
            Node node = nodeMap.get(key);
            node.value = value;
            updateFrequency(node);
            return ;
        }

        if(nodeMap.size() == capacity)
        {
            DoublyLinkedList minFreqList = freqMap.get(minFreq);
            Node removeNode = minFreqList.removeTail();
            nodeMap.remove(removeNode.key);
        }
        Node newNode = new Node(key, value);
        nodeMap.put(key, newNode);
        freqMap.computeIfAbsent( 1, k -> new DoublyLinkedList()).addToHead(newNode);

        minFreq = 1;
    }

    public void updateFrequency(Node node)
    {
        int oldFreq = node.freq;

        DoublyLinkedList oldList = freqMap.get(oldFreq);
        oldList.remove(node);

        if(oldFreq == minFreq && oldList.size == 0)
        {
            minFreq++;
        }

        node.freq++;

        freqMap.computeIfAbsent(node.freq, k -> new DoublyLinkedList())
                .addToHead(node);
    }
}




# LFU Cache Algorithm and Code Explanation

## LFU Cache Idea

LFU means:

```text
Least Frequently Used
```

When the cache is full, we remove the key that was used the least number of times.

If two keys have the same frequency, we remove the least recently used key among them.

So LFU Cache needs to track two things:

```text
1. Frequency count
2. Recent order inside the same frequency
```

---

## Data Structures Used

We use:

```java
Map<Integer, Node> nodeMap;
```

This stores:

```text
key -> actual node
```

So we can get any key in `O(1)` time.

We also use:

```java
Map<Integer, DoublyLinkedList> freqMap;
```

This stores:

```text
frequency -> list of nodes with that frequency
```

Example:

```text
freq = 1: head <-> 5 <-> 2 <-> tail
freq = 2: head <-> 4 <-> tail
freq = 3: head <-> 1 <-> tail
```

Inside each frequency list:

```text
head side = most recently used
tail side = least recently used
```

We also keep:

```java
int minFreq;
```

This stores the lowest frequency currently present in the cache.

When the cache is full, we remove from:

```java
freqMap.get(minFreq).removeTail();
```

---

# Algorithm

## get(key)

```text
1. If key is not present:
   return -1.

2. Get the node from nodeMap.

3. Since this key is used now, increase its frequency:
   - Remove it from its old frequency list.
   - If old frequency was minFreq and the old list becomes empty,
     increase minFreq.
   - Increase node.freq.
   - Add node to the head of the new frequency list.

4. Return node.value.
```

---

## put(key, value)

```text
1. If capacity is 0:
   return.

2. If key already exists:
   - Update node.value.
   - Increase its frequency using updateFrequency().
   - Return.

3. If cache is full:
   - Go to freqMap.get(minFreq).
   - Remove the tail node from that list.
   - Remove that node's key from nodeMap.

4. Create a new node with freq = 1.

5. Add it to nodeMap.

6. Add it to freqMap.get(1).

7. Set minFreq = 1.
```

---

# Full Code

```java
class LFUCache {

    class Node {
        int key;
        int value;
        int freq;
        Node prev;
        Node next;

        public Node(int key, int value) {
            this.key = key;
            this.value = value;
            this.freq = 1;
        }
    }

    class DoublyLinkedList {
        Node head;
        Node tail;
        int size;

        public DoublyLinkedList() {
            head = new Node(0, 0);
            tail = new Node(0, 0);

            head.next = tail;
            tail.prev = head;

            size = 0;
        }

        public void addToHead(Node node) {
            node.next = head.next;
            node.prev = head;

            head.next.prev = node;
            head.next = node;

            size++;
        }

        public void remove(Node node) {
            node.prev.next = node.next;
            node.next.prev = node.prev;

            size--;
        }

        public Node removeTail() {
            if (size == 0) return null;

            Node node = tail.prev;
            remove(node);

            return node;
        }
    }

    int capacity;
    int minFreq;

    Map<Integer, Node> nodeMap;
    Map<Integer, DoublyLinkedList> freqMap;

    public LFUCache(int capacity) {
        this.capacity = capacity;
        this.minFreq = 0;

        this.nodeMap = new HashMap<>();
        this.freqMap = new HashMap<>();
    }

    public int get(int key) {
        if (!nodeMap.containsKey(key)) {
            return -1;
        }

        Node node = nodeMap.get(key);

        updateFrequency(node);

        return node.value;
    }

    public void put(int key, int value) {
        if (capacity == 0) return;

        if (nodeMap.containsKey(key)) {
            Node node = nodeMap.get(key);
            node.value = value;

            updateFrequency(node);

            return;
        }

        if (nodeMap.size() == capacity) {
            DoublyLinkedList minFreqList = freqMap.get(minFreq);

            Node removedNode = minFreqList.removeTail();

            nodeMap.remove(removedNode.key);
        }

        Node newNode = new Node(key, value);

        nodeMap.put(key, newNode);

        freqMap
            .computeIfAbsent(1, k -> new DoublyLinkedList())
            .addToHead(newNode);

        minFreq = 1;
    }

    private void updateFrequency(Node node) {
        int oldFreq = node.freq;

        DoublyLinkedList oldList = freqMap.get(oldFreq);

        oldList.remove(node);

        if (oldFreq == minFreq && oldList.size == 0) {
            minFreq++;
        }

        node.freq++;

        freqMap
            .computeIfAbsent(node.freq, k -> new DoublyLinkedList())
            .addToHead(node);
    }
}
```

